fields.Title: PLAZA / THE GARDENER
fields.Description: The Gardener stands on the corner of Whirling and is there to help you navigate the streets of Martinaise. Later it turns out she's a Union spy. You get to know from here that Joyce is in town.

fields.Dialogue Text: Pier? Buildings? Apartments? You should *explore*, maybe scale a wall?

fields.Title: You: ""The body is down.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "The body is down."

fields.Dialogue Text: "The body is gone."

fields.Dialogue Text: "You're black."

fields.Dialogue Text: "Me? I'm just a gardener."

fields.Dialogue Text: Nothing to see here. Just a regular law official reacting to every day stimuli. Nothing noteworthy here.

fields.Dialogue Text: "Of course. What can I help you with?"

fields.Dialogue Text: "Of course, I won't hold you back." She wipes her brow with the canary yellow glove.

fields.Dialogue Text: "What is on the other side of the canal?"

fields.Dialogue Text: Yeah, keep her in the *loop*. It's strangely enjoyable to report back on the minute progress you've made. Even to strangers.

fields.Dialogue Text: "I'm a night hawk, what can I say?" She flashes a smile.

fields.Dialogue Text: There's a little meanness in that smile.

fields.Title: Perception (Smell): "Even all the way over here, there's..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Even all the way over here, there's a drop of death in the spring air.

fields.Title: You: "No. I don't want to say that."
fields.Dialogue Text: No. I don't want to say that.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""No need to worry," the lieutenant..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "No need to worry," the lieutenant steps in, "we're not saying you did."

fields.Dialogue Text: "Oh. Okay." She doesn't quite know what to say. "Thanks for keeping me in the know, sir."

fields.Title: You: "Shake it off, you seem to be under..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Shake it off, you seem to be under some kind of cold spell...

fields.Dialogue Text: "I have some questions for you."

fields.Dialogue Text: "It's raining again..." The young woman resting by the wheelbarrow sighs.
fields.Alternate1: "It's raining again..." The young woman looks up at the overladen sky.

fields.Title: You: ""My partner told me you may have am..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "My partner told me you may have ammonia -- can I have some?"

fields.Title: You: ""What is in the East?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "What is in the East?"

fields.Dialogue Text: "The harbour gates. Some kind of commotion, I think? I don't follow the local politics." She shrugs. "A Frittte store too."

fields.Dialogue Text: "What is in the West?"

fields.Dialogue Text: You didn't say she wrote it, you asked what it was doing there.

fields.Dialogue Text: No! Do *not* keep this random civilian in any loops.

fields.Dialogue Text: "Snow has nutrients in it -- helps everything green up in the spring. At least that's what my grandma always told me." She smiles shyly.

fields.Dialogue Text: "Mhmh." She looks at her wheelbarrow, where the snow is slowly melting.

fields.Dialogue Text: "Are you by any chance keeping an eye on us?"
fields.Alternate1: "Are you by any chance keeping an eye on me?"

fields.Dialogue Text: "We should probably proceed with our business in Martinaise." The lieutenant interrupts her, turning to you. "Unless you didn't have any more *official* questions?"

fields.Dialogue Text: "Do you listen to disco?"
fields.Alternate1: "Do you listen to disco? I need some fresh jams to get out of this rut."

fields.Dialogue Text: "What about the other sign. *Pigs go home*? Who are these pigs?"

fields.Dialogue Text: Even if she didn't write it, she should CLEAN IT.

fields.Title: The Gardener: ""Like gone-gone?" The girl repeats,..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Like gone-gone?" The girl repeats, her face beaming with appreciation.

fields.Dialogue Text: "Yes." She looks relieved. "It smells pretty bad, so I have to take breaks."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Yes. A representative of the harbo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yes. A representative of the harbour. She should have set up operations nearby."

fields.Dialogue Text: "What is in the South?"

fields.Title: You: ""Maybe." (Nod.) "Pleased to meet yo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Maybe." (Nod.) "Pleased to meet you, Just A Gardener. I have another question."

fields.Dialogue Text: Squint your eyes and look at her intently.

fields.Dialogue Text: Are you entirely sure you're black as *fuck*? You should really check out that mirror thing. For now, go with she's black. It's important to the case.

fields.Title: You: "So what? I'm also black."
fields.Dialogue Text: So what? I'm also black.

fields.Dialogue Text: I don't know -- what's the problem? You're just *reacting to stimuli*.

fields.Title: You: ""Good to meet you, Just-A-Gardener...."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Good to meet you, Just-A-Gardener. Another question then."

fields.Dialogue Text: "Some shops and a bridge. The canal bridge leads to the coast, but it's broken, I think? Some kind of accident probably."

fields.Title: Empathy: "She's not okay with it. It's a disp..."
fields.Dialogue Text: She's not okay with it. It's a display of power and she feels threatened by it. You don't know why.

fields.Dialogue Text: The place looks the part. There's graffito everywhere and the traffic jam behind you is completely *unregulated*.

fields.Title: You: ""You could clean it up if you get a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You could clean it up if you get a chance. Be a citizen -- be a winner."

fields.Title: Empathy: "There's discomfort. She stops mid s..."
fields.Dialogue Text: There's discomfort. She stops mid sentence.

fields.Title: Perception (Sight): "She's black."
fields.Dialogue Text: She's black.

fields.Dialogue Text: "We should proceed with our business in Martinaise." The lieutenant turns to you.

fields.Dialogue Text: "I don't know... the abandoned kind? It used to gather every spring, but there's nothing to do there now. Just drug addicts."

fields.Dialogue Text: "Uh... I'm gonna say no."

fields.Dialogue Text: "You're back."

fields.Title: The Gardener: ""Okay.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Okay."

fields.Dialogue Text: Odd...

fields.Dialogue Text: "Oh?" She cranes her neck. "Well, I didn't write it there. I'm just sitting here."

fields.Dialogue Text: You get a strange feeling, looking at that smile. It spoils the moment. It is disingenuous.

fields.Dialogue Text: What are you waiting for, ask about the disco already. You need some fresh jams to get out of this rut.

fields.Title: The Gardener: ""In heaven?" A quick smile. "Thank..."

fields.Dialogue Text: "I didn't say you wrote it."

fields.Dialogue Text: All you can see is the fact that her skin is a different colour from yours. That's literally all. You're gonna have to run with that.

fields.Alternate2: All you can see is the fact that her skin is a different colour from yours. That's literally all. You're gonna have to run with that.

fields.Dialogue Text: "It is, because he sent you to harass me, didn't he? You shouldn't listen to him." She points to the defaced sign above her on the corner. "It was probably him, who wrote that."

fields.Title: The Gardener: "There's silence. The smallest of sm..."
fields.Dialogue Text: There's silence. The smallest of smiles.

fields.Title: The Gardener: ""What does that mean?" She doesn't..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "What does that mean?" She doesn't flinch.

fields.Title: You: ""It's alright, I'm just asking.""

fields.Dialogue Text: "As you *probably* know, there's a corpse hanging from a tree there. It smells pretty bad. So I have to take breaks."
fields.Alternate1: "As you already know, there's a corpse there. Hanging from a tree. It smells pretty bad, so I have to take breaks."

fields.Title: The Gardener: ""I'm working.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "I'm working."

fields.Title: The Gardener: ""Sure, keep them. I have another pa..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Sure, keep them. I have another pair." She hands you the rubber gloves with no visible annoyance.

fields.Title: The Gardener: ""Just coast. There's a little fishi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Just coast. There's a little fishing village there... and a fish market. But that got closed down ages ago."

fields.Title: The Gardener: ""What do you mean?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "What do you mean?"

fields.Title: Reaction Speed: "Salts? Ammonium salts? Perhaps usef..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Salts? Ammonium salts? Perhaps useful for later.

fields.Title: You: "The plaza?"
fields.Dialogue Text: The plaza?

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""I understand -- the RCM isn't welc..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I understand -- the RCM isn't welcome here and the locals want to keep an eye on us."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""That was the last time, miss." He..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "That was the last time, miss." He looks at you with a stern expression. "Our questioning here is concluded. Let's go."

fields.Title: You: ""Nothing.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Nothing."

fields.Title: You: ""The police need directions.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "The police need directions."

fields.Title: Perception (Sight): "Uhm... are you sure? In the mirror..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Uhm... are you sure? In the mirror it looked like you were pink, grey and more than a little reddish.

fields.Title: Perception (Sight): "You *really* need to take a look at..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You *really* need to take a look at that mirror upstairs.

fields.Title: You: ""There's more to you than that.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "There's more to you than that."

fields.Title: You: ""Who are you exactly?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Who are you exactly?"

fields.Title: The Gardener: ""Okay.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Okay."

fields.Title: Authority: "She's probably not gonna do it."
fields.Dialogue Text: She's probably not gonna do it.

fields.Title: You: "An entrance to the yard?"
fields.Dialogue Text: An entrance to the yard?

fields.Title: You: ""So, what kind of music do you list..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "So, what kind of music do you listen to nowadays?"

fields.Title: Half Light: "Really? *None.* Maybe just a *tiny*..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Really? *None.* Maybe just a *tiny* bit of annoyance.

fields.Title: The Gardener: ""Oh... right." She scratches her ch..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Oh... right." She scratches her cheek. "But not from the yard. I understand."

fields.Title: You: "*Should* I say that?"
fields.Dialogue Text: *Should* I say that?

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""We should probably proceed with ou..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "We should probably proceed with our business in Martinaise." The lieutenant interrupts her, turning to you. "Unless you didn't have any more *official* questions?"

fields.Title: Empathy: "She doesn't like that *giant* boat...."
fields.Dialogue Text: She doesn't like that *giant* boat. Nor does she like the woman on it.

fields.Title: The Gardener: ""Is there?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Is there?"

fields.Title: Composure: "The quickness of the reply certainl..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The quickness of the reply certainly does not prove you wrong.

fields.Title: The Gardener: ""Hello again, officer. How are thin..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Hello again, officer. How are things?"

fields.Title: You: ""Where am I?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Where am I?"

fields.Title: You: ""Do you know where I could find the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Do you know where I could find the representative for Wild Pines?"

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Relax, miss. This is not an interr..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Relax, miss. This is not an interrogation. We are just checking some facts."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""You don't have to stay up because..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You don't have to stay up because of us."

fields.Title: The Gardener: ""Gone to heaven?" A quick smile. "T..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Gone to heaven?" A quick smile. "Thank you, officer. Looks like I'll get mint in the ground by April."

fields.Title: You: ""There's a corpse there, keeping yo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "There's a corpse there, keeping you from doing your work."

fields.Title: You: ""What kind of a fish market is this?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "What kind of a fish market is this?"

fields.Title: You: ""What is up in the North?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "What is up in the North?"

fields.Title: Empathy: "She seems more perplexed than threa..."
fields.Dialogue Text: She seems more perplexed than threatened.

fields.Title: Horrific Necktie: "Ask her about music -- it'll get th..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Ask her about music -- it'll get the convo flowing, don't worry!

fields.Title: The Gardener: ""Can you tell me when you've taken..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Can you tell me when you've taken him away then. Because I'm sort of waiting for *that*."

fields.Title: The Gardener: ""No, of course not! I don't underst..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "No, of course not! I don't understand what this is about..." She looks towards the yard and her expression clears.

fields.Title: The Gardener: ""Maybe you shouldn't be. I mean......"
fields.Dialogue Text: "Maybe you shouldn't be. I mean... you do your job, but that kid is beyond help. And he certainly won't help *you*." She shakes her head.

fields.Title: The Gardener: ""Yes. I'm tired.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yes. I'm tired."

fields.Title: You: ""Okay.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Okay."

fields.Title: The Gardener: ""I don't know..." She looks around...."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I don't know..." She looks around. "Whatever's on the radio I guess. What does this have to do with snow, or gardening in March?"

fields.Title: You: "No, those gloves aren't really my s..."
fields.Dialogue Text: No, those gloves aren't really my style. [Leave.]

fields.Title: The Gardener: ""No problem." She nods, brushing a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "No problem." She nods, brushing a fleck of soil off her cheek.

fields.Title: You: ""I'm... disorientated. I don't know..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I'm... disorientated. I don't know where I am."
fields.Alternate1: "I'm a bit disoriented. This is Revachol, right?"

fields.Title: You: ""Just tell me where we are, okay?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Just tell me where we are, okay?"

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "Stop looking at her, look around! W..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Stop looking at her, look around! What do you see?

fields.Title: You: ""You're black.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "You're black."

fields.Title: The Gardener: ""The kid did this, right? The red-h..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "The kid did this, right? The red-haired rat? Can't say a sentence without *f****t* or *kipt*... He's always giving me trouble."

fields.Title: The Gardener: ""It is, because he sent you to hara..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It is, because he sent you to harass me. He's playing you." She shakes her head. "He hates the police, okay? A lot of people do around here."

fields.Title: The Gardener: "She shifts in her seat awkwardly."
fields.Dialogue Text: She shifts in her seat awkwardly.

fields.Title: The Gardener: ""An autopsy? Wow. Sure, keep them."..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "An autopsy? Wow. Sure, keep them." She hands you the rubber gloves. "I have another pair."

fields.Title: Empathy: "She's relieved someone has come for..."
fields.Dialogue Text: She's relieved someone has come for it -- finally.

fields.Title: Perception (Sight): "She must be very diligent about the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: She must be very diligent about the glove-use, because her hands are clean and delicate.

fields.Title: Perception (Sight): "She must be very diligent about the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: She must be very diligent about the glove-use, because her hands are clean and delicate.

fields.Title: Authority: "No! Do *not* report back to this ra..."
fields.Dialogue Text: No! Do *not* report back to this random civilian about anything.

fields.Title: You: ""The grandma is a bit too much.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "The grandma is a bit too much."

fields.Title: The Gardener: ""Nitrogen and sulphur mostly." She..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Nitrogen and sulphur mostly." She points to the sky. "And whatever factories and aerostatics exhale too I guess."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""That's okay, miss -- do what you h..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "That's okay, miss -- do what you have to do." The lieutenant nods at you. "I think we're done here. Let's go."

fields.Title: The Gardener: ""Okay.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Okay."

fields.Title: You: ""Thank you." [Leave]"
fields.Dialogue Text: "Thank you." [Leave]

fields.Title: Empathy: "She's uncomfortable. Maybe you shou..."
fields.Dialogue Text: She's uncomfortable. Maybe you should drop this line of questioning.

fields.Title: The Gardener: ""Well... as you *probably* know, th..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Well... as you *probably* know, there's a corpse hanging from a tree there. It smells pretty bad. So I have to take breaks."
fields.Alternate1: "Well... as you already know there's a corpse there, hanging from a tree. It smells pretty bad. So I have to take breaks."

fields.Title: Perception (Sight): "What if I told you there's a *mirro..."
fields.Dialogue Text: What if I told you there's a *mirror* on your bathroom wall, upstairs? You *may* want to take a look.

fields.Title: The Gardener: ""I'm okay with it. Was there someth..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I'm okay with it. Was there something else?"

fields.Title: Empathy: "She would probably prefer not to go..."
fields.Dialogue Text: She would probably prefer not to go into it. It wasn't easy to pick up on either...

fields.Title: Shivers: "Rows of stalls under a broad roof,..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Rows of stalls under a broad roof, where silvery fish were heaped on newspapers. Water, water everywhere -- pouring from the heavens, in the shadow of the old church.

fields.Title: The Gardener: ""The RCM in Martinaise?" The young..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "The RCM in Martinaise?" The young woman looks up at you. "What can I help you with?"

fields.Title: Interfacing: "If there's a corpse, then you're go..."
fields.Dialogue Text: If there's a corpse, then you're going to need those gloves for the autopsy.

fields.Title: You: ""Do you listen to disco?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Do you listen to disco?"

fields.Title: You: ""Okay.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Okay."

fields.Title: You: ""Yes. What are you doing here?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yes. What are you doing here?"

fields.Title: The Gardener: ""Okay, well, I didn't," she leans b..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Okay, well, I didn't," she leans back, shoulders relaxing.

fields.Title: The Gardener: ""Well uh..." She points to her whee..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Well uh..." She points to her wheelbarrow, surprised at the question. "This might be the last snow we get. At least I hope so..."

fields.Title: Drama: "She feels interrogated now. It's ha..."
fields.Dialogue Text: She feels interrogated now. It's hard to say if she's lying.

fields.Title: You: ""That's not important right now.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "That's not important right now."

fields.Title: The Gardener: ""Yes, I'm black, how many times are..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yes, I'm black, how many times are you gonna say that?"

fields.Title: The Gardener: ""Sure thing." She narrows her eyes."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Sure thing." She narrows her eyes.
